The patch in the newer version changes the executor from `threadPool.executor(ThreadPool.Names.MANAGEMENT)` to `EsExecutors.DIRECT_EXECUTOR_SERVICE` and adds a deduplicator `SingleResultDeduplicator` that wraps the allocationStatsService.stats call executed on the management thread pool executor.

The class `SingleResultDeduplicator` exists in the older version and can be used for backporting.

The `EsExecutors.DIRECT_EXECUTOR_SERVICE` also exists in the older version.

The patch also removes the direct assignment of `this.allocationStatsService = allocationStatsService;` because the service is now wrapped in the deduplicator.

So the backport patch should:

- Change the executor in the super constructor call.
- Add a `managementExecutor` variable from the threadPool.management executor.
- Add a new field `allocationStatsSupplier` initialized with the SingleResultDeduplicator wrapping the allocationStatsService.stats call executed on the managementExecutor.
- Remove the direct assignment `this.allocationStatsService = allocationStatsService;`.
- Keep the rest unchanged.

The older version constructor has an additional parameter `IndexNameExpressionResolver indexNameExpressionResolver` passed to super, which is removed in the newer version, so we keep it in the backport.

The patch must keep the context lines as in the older version.

